   Housing Assessments}},
Journal = {{JOURNAL OF PLANNING EDUCATION AND RESEARCH}},
Abstract = {{This paper evaluates a citizen science initiative to assess housing
   conditions in multiple rural Georgia communities. Using technologies for
   digitized collection of volunteered geographic information (VGI) on
   property conditions and an online dashboard to analyze results, local
   housing teams identified the characteristics and prevalence of housing
   problems in their communities. Drawing from a pragmatist framework, we
   note how this process created new connections between local leaders and
   residents and brought attention to sometimes unexpected issues.
   Conversely, participation was uneven within local communities in ways
   that potentially limit the effectiveness of these local initiatives.}},
