   initially, to present an overview of cartography in Brazil through the
   analysis of the evolution of topographic mapping coverage in the
   country. For each of the main scales used, a coverage map was created.
   The analyzes reflect three different periods (until 1997, between 1998
   and 2007, after 2008) in order to relate how and to what degree, the
   creation of Brazilian National SDI (in 2008) had an impact on the
   mapping production in the country. Given the current panorama, as a
   final objective, this paper aims at to present proposals to leverage the
   coverage of this reference data. One of them is the use of new data
   sources such as Volunteered Geographic Information, especially in areas
