   reflect recent market activity or the full scope of the US rental
   market. To address this gap, we collected, cleaned, analyzed, mapped,
   and visualized eleven million Craigslist rental housing listings. The
   data reveal fine-grained spatial and temporal patterns within and across
   metropolitan housing markets in the United States. We find that some
   metropolitan areas have only single-digit percentages of listings below
