Abstract = {{The paper describes the application of real-time environmental
   monitoring, local and long-range transport dispersion modeling and
   Volunteered Geographic Information (VGI) systems that can improve the
   fast knowledge regarding the air pollution status to determine the
   actual outdoor conditions for living in a specific urban area. A case
   study using such techniques is presented fora pollution event with fine
   particulate matter (PM2 in Targoviste, Romania. PM2.5 time series were
