Abstract = {{Surface water quality monitoring (SWQM) provides essential information
   for water environmental protection. However, SWQM is costly and limited
   in terms of equipment and sites. The global popularity of social media
   and intelligent mobile devices with GPS and photography functions allows
   citizens to monitor surface water quality. This study aims to propose a
   method for SWQM using social media platforms. Specifically, a
   WeChat-based application platform is built to collect water quality
   reports from volunteers, which have been proven valuable for water
